> Hi,
> this problem maybe a gcc problem.
No its a programming error
> main() {
> 	int	i=0, *status;
                      ^^^^^^^
uninitialised pointer
> 		wait(status);
Then you pass it to wait.
Then quite predictibly things go boom
Try
	int i=0, status
and
	wait(&status)
